parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air suspension system can cause the vehicle to ride on its axle, leading to hard steering, rough riding, and increased risk of accidents, including rollover.
symptoms: The air suspension system falls down on the tire
the vehicle rides on its axle

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ignition Module Failure due to Excessive Heat
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition module can cause the vehicle to stall while driving, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the distributor cap or rotor shows signs of excessive heat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical short can cause a compartment fire under the dash, potentially spreading to other areas of the vehicle and putting occupants at risk of injury or death.
symptoms: Smoke or flames visible under the dash
warning lights or alarms on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure due to Broken Transmission Control Cable Linkage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission control cable linkage can cause the transmission to slip or fail to shift properly, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, or stranding.
symptoms: failure to shift into higher gears
transmission fluid appears dark or burnt
transmission control cable linkage is loose or broken.
